docs.abstract: The influential series, which fired the actor Jeffrey Tambor over sexual harassment allegations, will wrap up with a musical finale.
docs.snippet: The influential series, which fired the actor Jeffrey Tambor over sexual harassment allegations, will wrap up with a musical finale.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Last February, Jill and Faith Soloway were filming the final episode of “Transparent” here at Paramount Pictures, in the studio’s cavernous Stage 14. It was the last day of a 20-day shoot, and Judith Light, as the nettlesome matriarch Shelly Pfefferman, was tearing through “Your Boundary Is My Trigger,” a show tune-slash-primal scream about how thankless it is to be a mother, and how Shelly gives and gives and gives, and for what?

headline.main: After Times of Turmoil, ‘Transparent’ Goes Out Singing
